value.value: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in axons.
The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in a dendrite from the postsynapse towards the cell body.
The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in dendrites.
The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell body toward the postsynapse in dendrites.
Neurotransmitter receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane during synaptic transmission.
The directed movement of a ribonucleoprotein complex along microtubules in nerve cell dendrites.

label.value: regulation of postsynaptic neurotransmitter receptor activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in synaptic transmission. Modulation may be via an effect on ligand affinity, or effector function such as ion selectivity or pore opening/closing in ionotropic receptors.

label.value: exocytic insertion of neurotransmitter receptor to postsynaptic membrane

value.value: The exocytic fusion of neurotransmitter receptor containing vesicles with the postsynaptic membrane resulting in the integration of NT receptors, enabling them to participate in neurotransmitter reception. This process includes tethering and docking steps that prepare vesicles for fusion.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor transport to postsynaptic membrane

value.value: The directed movement of neurotransmitter receptor to the postsynaptic membrane in transport vesicles.

label.value: anterograde dendritic transport of neurotransmitter receptor complex

value.value: The directed movement of a neurotransmitter receptor complex along microtubules in nerve cell dendrites towards the postsynapse.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins in the postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton.
The postsynapse of a neuromuscular junction. In vertebrate muscles this includes the motor end-plate, consisting of postjunctional folds of the sarcolemma.
Synaptic transmission that results in an excitatory postsynaptic potential.
A synapse that uses glutamate as a neurotransmitter.
A synapse that uses acetylcholine as a neurotransmitter.
A synapse that uses GABA as a neurotransmitter. These synapses are typically inhibitory.
Combining with glutamate and transmitting a signal from one side of the membrane to the other by activating an associated G-protein, initiating a change in cell activity.

label.value: kainate selective glutamate receptor signaling pathway

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by glutamate binding to an kainate-selective glutamate receptor on the surface of the target cell, followed by the movement of ions through a channel in the receptor complex, ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

A dense core vesicle (granule) that is part of a neuron. These vesicles typically contain neuropeptides. They can be found in all parts of neurons, including the soma, dendrites, axonal swellings (varicosities) and synaptic terminals.
Any vesicle-mediated transport that occurs in a synapse.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a neuronal dense core vesicle.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a neuronal dense core vesicle.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a presynapse.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a postsynapse.

label.value: regulation of postsynaptic membrane neurotransmitter receptor levels

value.value: Any process that regulates the the local concentration of neurotransmitter receptor at the postsynaptic membrane.
A cellular component that consists of an indeterminate number of proteins or macromolecular complexes, organized into a regular, higher-order structure such as a polymer, sheet, network or a fiber.
A polymeric supramolecular structure.
Cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a neuropeptide.

label.value: retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Modulation of synaptic transmission by cell-cell signaling across the synaptic cleft from postsynapse to presynapse, mediated by a neuropeptide.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Enables the transmembrane transfer of an inorganic cation by a channel that opens when a specific ligand has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.
The giant, cup-shaped axon terminal of a vestibular afferent neuron, serving as a post-synaptic contact to a type I hair cell.
The movement of a cellular component as a result of microtubule polymerization.

A microtubule-based process that results in the transport of organelles, other microtubules, or other cellular components. Examples include motor-driven movement along microtubules and movement driven by polymerization or depolymerization of microtubules.
The transport of a protein driven by polymerization of a microtubule to which it is attached.
A microtubule-based process that results in the transport of proteins.
The regulated release of dopamine from the somatodendritic compartment (cell body or dendrites) of a neuron.
The regulated release of dopamine from an axon.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins in the presynaptic actin cytoskeleton.
The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a presynapse.

label.value: regulation of exocytic insertion of neurotransmitter receptor to postsynaptic membrane

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of exocytic fusion of neurotransmitter receptor containing vesicles into the postsynaptic membrane.
Cell-cell signaling in which the ligand is carried between cells by an exosome.
Transynaptic signaling in which the ligand is carried across the synapse by an exosome.
The intermediate filament cytoskeleton that is part of a postsynapse.

label.value: postsynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the postsynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.

label.value: presynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the presynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a presynapse.
A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a postsynapse.
Any process that modulates the physical form of a presynapse.
Any process that modulates the physical form of a postsynapse.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of trans-synaptic signaling.
